{"id":40,"date":"2024-06-03T15:16:40","date_gmt":"2024-06-03T20:16:40","guid":{"rendered":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/?page_id=40"},"modified":"2025-02-21T16:06:00","modified_gmt":"2025-02-21T22:06:00","slug":"report-it","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/report-it/","title":{"rendered":"Report It"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>This office offers many services to prevent hazing at Grambling State University. However, should any student find themselves the victim of hazing, there are ample resources and avenues of support available at the University.</p>\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <div class=\"ua_callout ua_context--info ua_layout--flow\">\n        <h2 class=\"ua_callout_title\"><span class=\"fa fa-circle-info\" title=\"Info\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n                <span class=\"ua_visually-hidden\">Info</span>Need emergency services?</h2>\n\n<p>If you are in an emergency and need immediate assistance, call 911 or contact the Grambling State Police Department (GSUPD) at <a href=\"tel:+13182742222\">318-274-2222</a>.</p>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n<p>The following offices offer opportunities to report hazing activity at Grambling State University.</p>\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"#location-osel\">Student Engagement</a></div>\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"#location-counseling\">Counseling Center</a></div>\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"#location-titleix\">Civil Rights & Title IX</a></div>\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"#location-conduct\">Student Conduct</a></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper  \"><div class=\"ua_layout--grid\" style=--grid-column-count:2>\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\" id=\"location-osel\">Office of Student Engagement and Leadership</h2>\n\n<p>The Office of Student Clubs and Organizations reports to the Dean of the Student Experience Office, which provides assistance and case management for students facing crisis while on campus. Students who find themselves victims of hazing may be able to access support from this office.</p>\n<p><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href=\"tel:+13182743334\">318-274-3334</a><br><strong>Location:</strong> Favrot Student Union, Room 218<br><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=Favrot+Student+Union+218+Grambling+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Get directions</a></p>\n\n</div></article>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\" id=\"location-counseling\">Counseling Center</h2>\n\n<p>If you or someone you know has been hazed and is struggling mentally because of it, the Counseling Center at GSU can help. The Counseling Center offers several counseling methods to all GSU students.</p>\n<p>Students can book individual counseling appointments (Monday through Friday, 8 a.m. - 5 p.m.) or call <a href=\"tel:+13182743163\">318-274-3163</a> or <a href=\"tel:+13182743277\">318-274-3277</a>.<br><strong>Location:</strong> Foster-Johnson, Room 113, Comp Counseling Center<br><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=Foster+Johnson+Hall+Room+113+Grambling+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Get directions</a></p>\n\n</div></article>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\" id=\"location-titleix\">Office of Civil Rights and Title IX</h2>\n\n<p>The Office of Civil Rights and Title IX at GSU offers counseling and advocacy services for victims of interpersonal violence. If you or someone you know has become a victim of interpersonal violence through hazing, see how the Title IX Office can help.</p>\n<p>If you are not sure whether you are a victim of interpersonal violence, review <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/titleIX/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">File a General Complaint - Procedures</a> or the <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/titleIX/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Power-Based Violence/Title IX/Sexual Misconduct Incident Report Form</a> for more insight. The office also offers free, confidential, and voluntary counseling.</p>\n\n</div></article>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\" id=\"location-conduct\">Office Student Conduct Resources</h2>\n\n<p>Please contact: The Office of Student Conduct, Grambling State University, 403 Main St, PO Box 4309, Grambling, LA 71245.<br><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href=\"tel:+13182747782\">(318) 274-7782</a><br><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"mailto:turnert@gram.edu\">turnert@gram.edu</a><br><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=403+Main+St+Grambling+LA+71245\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Get directions</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://cm.maxient.com/reportingform.php?GrambingStateUniv&amp;layout_id=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Incident Report Form</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/judicial-affairs/contact.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Authorization for Release of Information</a><br>\n<a href=\"../index.html%3Fp=24.html\">Student Code of Conduct</a><br>\n<a href=\"../index.html%3Fp=40.html\">Report Hazing Here</a></p>\n\n</div></article>\n    </div>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>All members of the campus community have a duty to promptly report good faith concerns about potential hazing impacting another member of the campus community. Specifically, if any such individual holds firsthand knowledge about hazing, whether that hazing has already occurred or is set to occur in the future, they have a duty to make [&hellip;]</p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"hero_blocks":"","sidebar_menu":"","sidebar":false,"sidebar_type":"select","hero":false,"title_alignment":"left","title_width":"standard","footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-40","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/40","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/types/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/comments?post=40"}],"version-history":[{"count":18,"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/40/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":634,"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/40/revisions/634"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/media?parent=40"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}}